<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Tops Chinese Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Hunter handed a 90-76
home defeat to Zhejiang Squirrels at the 19th round to keep its
top place at the Chinese basketball league on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
August First Rocketes remained second following its 89-76 home
victory over Shandong Flaming Bulls 89-76.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang put up a brilliant game in the first half and
outscored the more fancied rival 41-38 at the interval.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning quickened its pace in the second half. Li Xiaoyong
and Hu Qinglong, both on the Chinese national team, are heroes for
the visitors' comeback victory.
</P>
<P>
Led by veterans Adijiang and Liu Yudong, August First led over
Shandong 48-38 at the halftime.
</P>
<P>
With too many errors plus a poor percentage, Shandong saw
helplessly the host team run away on the scoreboard.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning topped the standings with a record of 17 wins against
two losses. August First, also with a 17-2 record, had to finish
second because it had lost to Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
Shandong placed third with 13 wins against six defeats.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Oriental, which lost to Lianhang Eagles 68-86 on
Sunday, was fourth with a 12-7 record.
</P>
<P>
Lianhang, trailing 33-44 at halftime, broke its rival's rhythm
with a desperately offensive game at the second half to complete
an upset victory.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, Beijing Duck beat Jinan Army Pegasus
81-77, Shenyang Army Lions downed Guangdong Tigers 86-56 and
Jiangsu Nangang routed Sichuan Panda 100-85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
