<HEADLINE> Thailand Beats Hong Kong 5-0 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Thailand won the doubles and
the two reverse singles on Sunday to complete a 5-0 victory over
Hong Kong in their Davis Cup Asia-Oceania zone group two first
round tie.
</P>
<P>
In the doubles match, Thailand's Thanakorn Srichaphan and
Narathorn Srichaphan beat Hong Kong's Graeme Foster and Mark
Ferreira 6-1, 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Vittaya Samrej of Thailand edged Ferreira 6-2, 6-2 in the first
reverse singles and his teammate Vorapol Thongkhamchoo downed
Wayne Wong 6-3, 7-6 (7-2) in the other reverse singles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
