<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Meets UNDP Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano today talked with Deputy Director of the Untied Nations
Development Program (UNDP), Ellen Sirleaf, over how best can UNDP
projects be implemented in the country.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Antonio Matonse said Sirleaf had signed
two new aid projects with relevant local authorities, which would
provide 11 million U.S. Dollars of development assistance to
Mozambique to improve its road condition and environment.
</P>
<P>
Sirleaf, who is also director of UNDP's African Regional
Bureau, told Chissano that UNDP has been implementing a
development program worth 150 million U.S. Dollars in the
southern African country which covers agricultural development,
poverty relief and administration management, etc., according to
Matonse.
</P>
<P>
Sirleaf, who had during the visit inspected some of the UNDP
projects under implementation, is scheduled to end her four-day
tour in Mozambique later today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
