<HEADLINE> Greece to Launch Tourism Promotion Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Greece will launch a promotion
campaign next week to project the country's tourism product
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Budgeted at six billion drachmas (about 24 million U.S.
dollars), Greece's National Tourism Organization (EOT) will use
the mass media as the main tool to get its message across.
</P>
<P>
The campaign will start from two major markets of Germany and
UK. Approximately 600 million drachmas (2.4 million U.S. dollars)
will be spent on the German market, and will be channeled into
television -- including sponsorship of the weather report on SAT1
channel and magazines.
</P>
<P>
EOT's spending in Germany will be heavier than in any other
European country, an outcome attributed to Germany's high
advertising rates, which are the contnent's steepest.
</P>
<P>
About 470 million drachmas (1.88 million U.S. dollars) will be
injected into the UK market.
</P>
<P>
EOT will also place strong emphasis on the U.S. market, where
some 400 million drachmas (1.6 million U.S. dollars) are expected
to be spent. EOT's marketing strategy in the U.S. will focus on
high-income earners.
</P>
<P>
Apart from the aforementioned markets, EOT will also inject
significant amounts into France, Austria, Russia, Italy, Sweden,
Yugoslavia and Canada.
</P>
<P>
The promotion campaign will come in two waves, the first in
this month, the other in May at the beginning of the Summer
season, at a time when many prospective tourists make their travel
plans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
