<HEADLINE> Iranian Foreign Minister on Ties with US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Ali
Akbar Velayati said here today that Iran would not do anything
for rapprochement between Tehran and Washington.
</P>
<P>
Velayati was quoted by the Persian evening paper Resalat as
saying that the question of relations between Iran and the United
States is one of the most important political issues.
</P>
<P>
"The decision-making in this regard is not at the disposal of
an ordinary person or the Foreign Ministry, it is the decision
of Iran's Islamic system," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister said that Iran's Supreme Leader
Ali Khamenei "has emphasized that we do not want to have any
kind of ties with the United States."
</P>
<P>
"The guideline is very clear and the Foreign Ministry would
not do anything outside the prescription," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Observers said that Velayati made the statement in a response
to media reports that Qatar is trying to mediate between Tehran
and Washington.
</P>
<P>
A senior Arab diplomat said in Doha that Qatar has undertaken
mediation efforts between the United States and Iran to smooth
relations between the two countries and reduce tension in the
Persian Gulf region.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat said that Qatar's Emir Sheikh Hamad Ben Khalifa
al-Thani sent a letter to Iranian President Rafsanjani, urging an
easing of tension between Tehran and Washington.
</P>
<P>
A similar letter was delivered to U.S. President Bill Clinton
by Qatar's ambassador to Washington through the State
Department.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the mediation efforts, Velayati said that "the
reason for the confrontation between Iran and the United States
is that the U.S. wants to interfere in Iran's internal affairs
just as before the victory of the Islamic revolution in the
country."
</P>
<P>
The United States pursues a dual-containment policy toward
Iran and Iraq. It has imposed sanction on Iran and even
threatened to launch military strike against Iranian targets.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
