<HEADLINE> Iranian Oil Minister to Visit Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 16 (Xinhua) -- The Iranian Minister of
Petroleum Gholam Reza Aqazadeh will pay a two-day visit to Kuwait
on February 23 to discuss cooperation in the oil field.
</P>
<P>
The visit, at the invitation of Kuwaiti Oil Minister Issa
Mohammed Al-mazidi, is "aimed at strengthening bilateral relations
in the oil fields and petroleum industries," a statement released
by the Iranian Embassy here said today.
</P>
<P>
Oil relations between the two countries have witnessed
remarkable development lately, the statement said, noting that
Iran signed a contract last month to purchase kerosin and benzin
from the state-owned Kuwait Oil Company.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait and Iran are two major oil producing countries in
the world. Kuwait has a proven oil reserve of about 80
billion barrels and its current crude production is 2 million
barrels per day with a daily oil refining capacity of
700,000 barrels. Iran's oil refining capacity is estimated at
1.24 million barrels per day.
</P>
<P>
Officials from Kuwait Oil Company visited Iran a week ago for
examining possibility of cooperation on oil, petroleum, gas and
petrochemical industries as well as joint investment, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
It said "Iran is ready to put its oil technical services,
engineering and experience under Kuwait's disposal."
</P>
<P>
The statement also said Aqazadeh would convey a message from
Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani to the Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah.
</P>
<P>
Iran recently expressed hope to boost cooperation in various
fields with the Arab Gulf countries. 
</P>
