<HEADLINE> Rose Production on Increase in East, Southern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Rose production is increasing
in east and southern Africa with Zimbabwe and Kenya playing a
leading role, the Export Flower Growers Association of Zimbabwe
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The prediction was based on recent surveys conducted by the
association, which showed that the five main producing countries
grew 440 hectares of roses.
</P>
<P>
During the 1995/96 horticultural season, Zimbabwe cultivated
229 hectares of roses, while Kenya cultivated 192 hectares.
Zambia, Uganda and Tanzania cultivated 45, 34 and 30 hectares,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The five countries produced a total of 530 hectares of rose in
the 1995/96 season, 21.3 percent up from that of the previous
year. 
</P>
