<HEADLINE> Albright Arrives in Paris on Her First Visit in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The United States Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright arrived at Paris this afternoon from
Germany, on her first official visit to France since she was sworn
in last month.
</P>
<P>
Albright will discuss with French President Jacques Chirac,
Prime Minister Alain Juppe, and Foreign Minister Herve de Charette
a series of international issues, priorly NATO expansion,
NATO-Russia relations and Europeanization of NATO's South Command.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, said French Foreign Ministry, French
officials will again raise the issue of Europeanization of the
NATO's Naples-based South Command, which Washington has rejected.
</P>
<P>
France is expecting to solve some disputes within the NATO over
how to negotiate a charter with Russia over NATO's eastward
expansion, before a NATO summit is held in Madrid in July, said
officials.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process, the crisis in the Great Lakes
region in central Africa, and the situation in former Yugoslavia
are also expected to be prominent topics between U.S. and French
officials.
</P>
<P>
The marathon journey of the new U.S. top diplomat, which is
taking her to nine European and Asian nations, will also allow
Albright to get acquainted with her counterparts in the major
international players of the world.
</P>
<P>
The local daily, Le Figaro, said that Albright is expected to
impose an energetic style which is totally different from one of
prudence adopted by her predecessor, Warren Christopher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
