<HEADLINE> Palestinians Accuses Israel of Violating Fishing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian Agriculture
Ministry has released a report listing violations by Israel of
signed Palestinian-Israeli agreement on fishing, the JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that according to the agreement, the area
allowed for fishing is 20 sea miles along the length of the
Gaza governorates coast.
</P>
<P>
However, since the beginning of 1996, the Israeli authorities
have confined the fishing area to only 12 sea miles, preventing
fishermen from operating beyond that point and even firing at
fishermen whenever they got near the 12-mile "border."
</P>
<P>
The Israeli navy boats randomly fired gunshots at Palestinian
boats even when they were not violating any regulations, said
the report. Many incidents took place in this respect.
</P>
<P>
The report pointed out that Palestinian fishing nets were
often ruined in points off the coast of Jewish settlements in
the southern part of the Gaza Strip. Fishermen were prevented
from laying their nets in that area despite the fact that this
area is allowed to fish in accordance with the agreement.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli authorities have also unilaterally decided to
restrict fishing near the border between the Gaza Strip and
Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
