to prevent a repeat of foul-ups at the Atlanta Summer Olympics
last year and install audiovisual equipment at venues and put in
extra seating for spectators.
</P>
<P>
NAOC vice chairman Goro Yoshimura told a news conference the
committee would not install floodlights expected to cost some 800
million yen (6.4 million U.S. dollars). 
