<HEADLINE> Reception Honors Sino-Mexican Diplomatic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The 25th anniversary of the
forging of China-Mexico diplomatic ties was celebrated this
evening with a reception held by the Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiaolin, vice-president of the association, said at the
function that the friendship between the people of the two
countries dates back to ancient times.
</P>
<P>
The friendly relations between the two countries have been
developed and grown stronger since the forging of the diplomatic
ties, Li said, adding that the frequent high level exchanges of
visits in recent years have helped ensure comprehensive and rapid
progress in bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Luis Wybo Alfaro, Mexico's ambassador to China, said that
Mexican people cherish brotherly friendship towards Chinese people
and both countries take the same stand in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that the bilateral relations will be
further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Shen Yun'ao, China's ambassador to Mexico, and Yang Jiechi,
assistant foreign minister also attended the reception.  
</P>
