<HEADLINE> Pak President Hopes Govt, Opposition to Cooperate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's President Farooq
Leghari today called upon the government and the opposition to
work together to "put the country back on tracks".
</P>
<P>
The government, the opposition and all the segments of society
to work together "as this is a golden opportunity to put the
country to the path of progress and advancement," Leghari told
reports after new Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif took oath today.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said the national economy was "a crisis-like situation
and it needs great discipline and prudent handling."
</P>
<P>
"We all have to sacrifice by tightening our belts all across,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the new government would handle the economy
competently.
</P>
<P>
The president said that it was the job of the executive to
handle the economy and other matters, the President's task is to
monitor the whole situation including economy because he looked at
things in a detached manner.
</P>
<P>
Though he had no experience of having worked with new Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif, they would establish and maintain good
relations, Leghari said.  
</P>
