<HEADLINE> More Concern Urged for Peoples' Immediate Interests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Projects that affect the
public's immediate interests should be done quickly and well, so
as to bring speedy benefits to the citizens and the local economy,
a senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Zhou Jiahua said this weekend during an inspection
tour in south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Zhou and other officials from Guangdong Province visited some
construction projects in Guangzhou, the capital city of Guangdong.
</P>
<P>
While viewing an apartment complex being constructed for those
whose per capita housing area is less than five sq m, Zhou said
that the project must be completed in a way that is satisfactory
to the public.
</P>
<P>
"The housing projects are closely related to the living of the
people, which is again closely related to the work efficiency in
society," he said.
</P>
<P>
The first construction phase of the complex, named Tongdewei in
the northwest Guangzhou, will house some 25,000 people when it is
finished.
</P>
<P>
Zhou delivered a speech to thousands of workers at the
construction site of the Guangzhou Subway, asking them to work
harder for the best interests of the local citizenry and economy.
</P>
