<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central Bank Bans Illegal Use of RMB Design </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Central Bank stressed
today that it is illegal to print and sell enlarged or miniature
versions of Renminbi (RMB) paper currency.
</P>
<P>
A leading official with the People's Bank of China pointed out
that RMB is the legal tender of China, and without bank
permission, no individual or unit is allowed to use the design of
RMB.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes people will become more aware of the law
and not buy the counterfeit bills. Meanwhile, he said people who
have information about the whereabouts of such shops that are
printing the bills have the responsibility to notify the police.
</P>
<P>
The color of some of the enlarged RMB bills found in a number
of areas is very similar to the originals, according to the
official.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the bank's Shenzhen branch and the local police
closed four illegal counterfeiting workshops in the booming south
China city, and confiscated a large amount of printed material.
</P>
<P>
After that, the People's Bank of China issued a notice asking
all the branches to cooperate with the local police, and for
industrial and commercial administration departments to crack down
on counterfeiting.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that 10 provinces and municipalities in the
country had retrieved over 100,000 phony bills by the end of last
August. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
