<HEADLINE> Saudis Warned not to Go Hunting Falcons in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 18 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today warned
its citizens not to go hunting for rare falcons and other
predatory birds in Kazakhstan in central Asia, official Saudi
Press Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a statement by the Saudi Foreign Ministry as
saying that it received a memorandum from Kazakhstan on the strict
measures against people who violate the rule by hunting and
smuggling the birds.
</P>
<P>
The memo said the law considered hunting the predatory birds
on its soil as a criminal act and might lead to imprisonment and
punishment. 
