<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Germans Die of Drug Abuse </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1,712 Germans died of
drug abuse last year, 147 more than in 1995, the first annual
increase in five years.
</P>
<P>
According to Eduard Lintner, the Bonn commissioner for
narcotics affairs, since 1991 when the use of
synthetically-produced drugs such as Ecstasy dramatically
increased, the number of deaths from drug abuse had been declining.
</P>
<P>
He said the number of first-time users of Ecstasy had grown by
half and police seizures of the narcotic jumped by 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of first-time users of so-called hard drugs such as
heroin and LSD had increased by 13 percent, Lintner said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
