<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Soccer Fans Charged in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Eight England soccer fans were
charged with public order offences on Monday following crowd
trouble during Leicester's FA Cup match with Chelsea on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Fighting broke out in a corner of the ground after Chelsea's
opening goal n the 16th minute of the fifth round match which
ended in a 2-2 draw.
</P>
<P>
It took 50 stewards and police 10 minutes to restore order and
separate rival supporters who were trading punches.
</P>
<P>
Football Association spokesman Steve Double said: "We will
await the reports of the match official and the police before
deciding what course of action should be taken."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Derbyshire police claim advance intelligence
prevented serious trouble at Saturday's FA Cup match between
Chesterfield and Premiership side Nottingham Forest.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-eight people were arrested before during and shortly
after the game which knocked Nottingham Forest out of the FA cup.
</P>
</TEXT>
