<HEADLINE> HK to Hold 7th Education, Careers Expo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to hold its 7th
Education and Careers Expo at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center from February 20 to 23, the Hong Kong Trade
Development Council (TDC) announced today.
</P>
<P>
More than 180 exhibitors, including local and overseas
educational institutes, private corporations, government
departments and professional associations will be present to
provide visitors with the most up-to-date information about
education and career opportunities.
</P>
<P>
This includes a large-scale delegation led by China's State
Education Commission, featuring 30 prestigious universities on the
mainland, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The Expo will also feature 60 seminars and 25 career video
shows highlighting diverse education and career opportunities
during the four-day fair.  
</P>
