<HEADLINE> National Flower Exhibition Opens in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- A three-day national flower
exhibition organized by the Export Promotion Bureau (EPB) was
opened today on the premises of Dhaka International Trade fair.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 nurseries and flower shops have set up 32 stalls
in the exhibition where varieties of roses and different colorful
seasonal flowers are on display.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time that such an exhibition is taking place
in Bangladesh with a view to encouraging growth of flowers as well
as their exports.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the exhibition, Commerce and Industries Minister
Tofail Ahmed said flowers had now been included as one of the
exportable items for Bangladesh, which is badly short of foreign
exchange reserve.
</P>
<P>
He said trial export of flowers has already been made to some
countries and for the first time from this year flower would be
exported on a commercial basis.
</P>
<P>
Faisal Ahmed Choudhury, vice chairman of the EPB, said there
was a good prospect for better quality flowers in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Some joint venture projects in this field had already been
started and foreign experts were assisting them now, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
