<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Spend 800 Million Dollars on Commonwealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia is going to
spend 800 million U.S. dollars to ensure Asia's first Commonwealth
Games to go on smoothly, according to the Malaysian top sport
official.
</P>
<P>
The next year's Commonwealth Games will be held in Kuala Lumpur
from September 11 to 21.
</P>
<P>
"We will ensure that no effort is spared towards hosting a
successful Commonwealth Games in 1998," said Minister of Youth and
Sports Muhyiddin Yassin.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is the first Asian host in the 68-year history of the
Games. The 15-event Games is expected to draw 6,000 athletes and
1,500 officials from 70 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Cricket, hockey, netball and rugby will make their debut at the
Games.  
