<HEADLINE> Angolan Airlines Passengers Top 400,000 Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- General Manager of the Angola
Airlines (TAAG) Miguel Costa today said his company transported
nearly 400,000 passengers in its domestic and international
flights in 1996, the Angola News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Costa told reporters in Angola's southern city Lubango that
among its 398,513 passengers, 116,087 were international
passengers, mainly for Europe, while 282,426 were domestic
passengers.
</P>
<P>
The volume of goods delivered by the TAAG reached more than
8,600 tons last year, he added.
</P>
<P>
The national airlines of Angola, with 4,297 employees, has now
only five Boeing 737s, six Fokers aircraft besides a Tristar
airplane rented from the Portuguese Airlines.
</P>
<P>
But the TAAG general manager said the priority of his company
this year is to improve its image, mainly enhancing its service
and training its staff.
</P>
<P>
It will also buy new aircraft to meet the demand at home and
abroad and challenges from other airlines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
