said disagreements between South Africa and the U.S. would not
damage the mutually beneficial relationship the two countries
currently enjoyed.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki was apparently referring to the controversy about South
Africa's proposed arms deal with Syria, which the U.S. labelled
as a "state sponsor of terrorism".
</P>
<P>
The South Africa-U.S. Bi-national Commission was established in
1995 and meets every six months by turn in both countries.
