<HEADLINE> Hong Kong to Host International Archives Workshop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong will hold a
five-day workshop on archives from tomorrow for the East Asian
Regional Branch of the International Council on Archives
(EASTICA).
</P>
<P>
Focusing on the understanding and use of standards in archival
descriptions recently adopted by the council, the workshop will
feature discussions, lectures, reports from participating
countries and regions and visits to local archival facilities.
</P>
<P>
It will mark the first attempt of cooperation among EASTICA
members in the standardization of archival descriptions to
facilitate future exchange of information, according to the Hong
Kong Public Records Office.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 experts from archives of China, Japan, South
Korea, Mongolia, Macao and Hong Kong will participate in the
workshop, which is to held at the Museum of History, Kowloon Park.
</P>
<P>
