<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC, Government Decision on Health Reform and Development (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Party committees and government should pay greater attention to
elementary health care in rural areas, where 900 million of
China's people live, and the cooperative health care system should
be further improved to include individual payments, public funds,
and governmental financial help, to ensure basic services for
farmers.
</P>
<P>
Health care networks in rural areas should improve their
service and management, and supplies of effective and quality
medicines should be ensured.
</P>
<P>
Health-care teams at the grass-roots level should be
consolidated and kept improving and by the turn of the century, 80
percent of rural doctors should have special training.
</P>
<P>
A pair-support system should be set up, where cities provide
medical support to corresponding townships and
villages. Intermediate-level urban doctors are asked to work in
county or township medical institutions for half a year or a full
year before being appointed to senior academic posts.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels should attach great importance to the
health work in poor rural areas or outlying regions inhabitated by
minority ethnic groups to help cure epidemic or infectious
diseases and fight the consequent poverty. The relatively
developed areas are encouraged to provide aid and support in this
regard.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
