<DOCNO> XIE19970217.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC, Government Decision on Health Reform and Development (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Government should allot adequate funds for prevention and
control of major diseases, which should focus on eliminating or
controlling epidemics and endemic diseases that seriously threaten
public health, and monitor general trends in the spread of
epidemic diseases abroad.
</P>
<P>
Organizations should improve prevention and control of
blood-transmitted diseases and non-infectious chronic diseases,
including cardiovascular and cerebro-vascular diseases and tumors.
</P>
<P>
They should improve their ability to deal with wounds and
injuries caused by accidents.
</P>
<P>
And the monitoring on the general trend of the spread of
epidemic diseases from both in and outside the country should be
stepped up.
</P>
<P>
Health departments should improve hygiene standards and the
monitoring of food, the environment, and prevention of
occupational diseases.
</P>
<P>
Health education is an important component part of national
education, and steps should be taken to promote "health education
among China's 900 million rural residents", and to spread a
knowledge of medicine.
</P>
<P>
People should be encouraged to live a healthy life and to
donate blood, and health departments should do their best to
improve the health of women and children, and further lower the
infant mortality rate, and that of pregnant women.
</P>
<P>
The health of the elderly and those with disabilities should be
improved by better health care rehabilitation methods.
</P>
<P>
The "Patriotic Health Campaign" is intended to get more people
involved in health work and should be carried out in both rural
and urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The state should increase investment in traditional medicine
and encourage a combination of traditional medicine and Western
medicine.
</P>
<P>
Traditional medicine as practiced by minority ethnic groups is
an integral part of traditional Chinese medicine, and materials in
this field should the studied, organized, collated, and
improved. The state will promote modernization of the production
of traditional medicines, and protect and develop herbal medicine
sources, and large-scaled intensive production should be developed.
</P>
<P>
Organizations should improve techniques and equipment and
provide more services. Education in traditional Chinese medicine
should be improved and more personnel trained, and the experience
of senior practitioners in this field should be handed down. .
</P>
<P>
Standards of quality in traditional Chinese medicine should be
drawn up and an open and competitive market developed.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970217.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC, Government Decision on Health Reform and Development (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Medical personnel are asked to increase technological
developments and basic and applied research to gradually catch up
with the developed countries in key medical fields and key medical
technology.
</P>
<P>
Medical personnel are asked to speed up the application of
scientific discoveries and to pay greater attention to the
utilization of medical information.
</P>
<P>
China will reform its medical research institutions by reducing
the number of staff and optimizing research projects and medical
colleges will improve education quality. Administrative personnel
are to be trained to cater to China's medical care development
needs.
</P>
<P>
The country hopes to implement system reform and safeguard
investment in and development of research institutions.
</P>
<P>
China will promote cooperation and exchanges with other
countries in the field of medicine by introducing technology and
experts from abroad and by sending medical personnel to developing
countries.
</P>
<P>
It is encouraging Chinese medical researchers or doctors
working abroad to work in China or provide services of any
kind. Formal education of medical workers in rural areas is also
being urged.
</P>
<P>
Much more attention will be paid to providing doctors with
better skills and with better professional ethics. Education in
professional ethics will be provided for other for medical
personnel. They should have superb professional ethics and be
devoted to their duties, providing better services for people.
</P>
<P>
Medical workers are urged to resist greed, materialism,
individualism, and any behavior that is not in society's interest.
</P>
<P>
A system of internal supervision is to the developed to correct
malpractice among doctors.
</P>
<P>
China will also improve the administration of development,
production, distribution, pricing, advertising, and use of
pharmaceutical products to guarantee their safe use. It will have
a medical development plan to coordinate the growth of
pharmaceutical products and medical care.
</P>
<P>
Technical improvements of the state-owned pharmaceutical
factories and better administration of those factories is also
called for, and pharmaceutical research and development is
encouraged to improve the competitive abilities of Chinese
products both in China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
China will improve and strengthen administration on the prices
of pharmaceuticals products by drafting a special price policy,
and their maximum prices will be restricted.
</P>
<P>
The country will encourage the production of high-quality lower
priced products that are included on the state's basic
pharmaceutical products list.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, China will tighten its examination and approval
process for imported pharmaceutical products and price controls on
them.
</P>
<P>
It will also crack down on the production and sale of fake or
shoddy pharmaceutical products, and close down illegal
pharmaceutical products markets or shops, and paying or receiving
kick-backs in the sale and purchase of pharmaceutical products is
an illegal act.
</P>
<P>
The country will support the development and production of
medical equipment and supplies and make an effort to improve their
quality.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970217.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC, Government Decision on Health Reform And Development (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Central and local governments will gradually increase input on
health care as the nation's economy grows year by year, and the
range of spending increases will not be less than financial
expenses. The central government also encourages the setting aside
of health care funds in other ways.
</P>
<P>
Public health organizations are non-profit and will continue to
enjoy tax breaks. Local governments bear responsibility in helping
reduce their burdens.
</P>
<P>
State-run health organizations rely on the government for
purchases of large appratuses and equipment. The government also
covers pensions of retired members of health organizations and
medical insurance for staff members.
</P>
<P>
The state budget will cover salaries of members of preventative
health care units and expenses of basic health care
business. Money raised from their paid services will be managed
separately from the financial allocation.
</P>
<P>
The government will provide subsidies for staff members of
medical service organizations as the organizations cover part of
their operational expenses through services.
</P>
<P>
Small town hospitals and those in poor rural areas will be
given more subsidities from the government. The central government
will also provide financial support for some key fields, such as
rural medicare, preventative health care, and traditional Chinese
medicine.
</P>
<P>
Preferential policies by the state will encourage donations by
enterprises, social groups, as well as individuals to health care
programs.
</P>
<P>
A foundation will be set up so that seriously ill people who
cannot afford the cost of medical care will receive proper
treatment.
</P>
<P>
Medical insurance funds at the township level should benefit
rural health care. Township enterprises and other economic groups
should pay for part of rural medicare and cooperative
medicare. Moreover, investment from overseas is also welcome in
the country's health care.
</P>
<P>
The government controls on medicare costs will be further
improved.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the government will add technical service fees to
medicare costs and increase the charge standard. And the fees for
use of large medical equipment for medical check-ups will be
lowered.
</P>
<P>
Governments should include the reform in medical service price
into their plans and implement them step by step and overcome the
international price problem in the next two or three years.
</P>
<P>
Local government should put medical care on its agenda and
discuss the issue at least one or two times a year and report on
health care reforms to the local people's congress at various
levels.
</P>
<P>
Reforms and development of health care should be listed on the
overall plan for national economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
The government will speed up legislation to guarantee healthy
growth in the country's health care. Laws and regulations on
public health, health-related products and health organizations be
further improved, and professionals will be further trained to
improve supervision and management. The public should be made
more aware of the law.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese People's Liberation Army and the Chinese People's
Armed Police are also being urged to serve the people by
supporting local health care work. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
