<DOCNO> XIE19970217.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU Chief Arrives in Cameroun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim Ahmed Salim has arrived
in Douala, economic capital of Cameroun to discuss matters about
the OAU with Camerounian leaders, reported the local radio today.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the press on his arrival yesterday, Salim said he
is in Cameroun to hold discussions with the current president of
the OAU, President of Cameroun Paul Biya on how to resolve the
numerable conflicts in the African continent and on some issues
concerning the OAU.
</P>
<P>
This is the second visit paid by Salim in nine months. He was
in Yaounde last July for the 32th summit of the OAU. 
