<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1500 GMT, February 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Visiting U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and
her Italian counterpart Lamberto Dini said today that the NATO
expansion should remain in process without spoiling the
relationship with Russia.
</P>
<P>
NATO should seek a "more structured relationship" with Russia,
leading to a possible "charter" or "statute" in which Russia would
have a greater political say in the process and would be more
involved in peace missions, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
MADRID -- The Liberal Union (UN) of Andorra today won victory
in the parliamentary election and its leader Marc Forne will
remain on the post of prime minister under the Constitution,
according to reports from Andorra la Vella.
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- More than 1,200 tons of crude oil has leaked out of
an oil pipeline Sunday night and 400 tons have flowed into the
River of Volga in Russia after an oil pipeline burst.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline running from Samara to the western Caucasian city
of Tichoreck burst at 11:15 a.m. (Moscow time) on Sunday in the
Ternovka village section in Engel's district of the Saratov
region, Russia's Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi said on Sunday that
the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO)'s eastward expansion
plan should be transparent and allow "full participation of all
members".
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with visiting United States Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright, Prodi also agreed with Albright on the
need of Russia's "constructive and responsible involvement" in
NATO's enlargement into central and eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greece has decided to form a special Rapid Action
Force (RAF) as part of its new defense strategy, Greek Defense
Minister Akis Tschatzopoulos announced here Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
The new move was intended to cope with what he claimed
"Turkey's challenge to Greek Sovereignty". 
</P>
