<HEADLINE> Shandong to Invest Heavily in River Clean-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- East China's coastal province of
Shandong will invest 800 million yuan (nearly 100 million US
dollars) this year to clean up the polluted Xiaoqinghe River.
</P>
<P>
Industrial development in recent years has caused heavy
pollution in the river, which originates in the western suburbs
of Jinan, the capital city of Shandong.
</P>
<P>
The river is 230 km long, passing through 18 counties and
cities including such important industrial cities as Zibo, Binzhou
and Dongying.
</P>
<P>
This year, the province plans to construct eight sluice gates
to control pollution, four lock gates for ships and 13 bridges
over the river, in addition to finishing the earthworks in the
main stream of the riverbed.
</P>
<P>
The river project started in November and will be completed in
three years. Total investment is estimated at 1.65 billion yuan
(some 200 million US dollars). 
</P>
