<HEADLINE> Israel Develops New Close-Range Radar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Israel Aircraft
Industries (IAI) has devised a new radar for the detection of
close-range ground and air threats, The Jerusalem Post reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The new radar, called EL/M-2129, is a ground-based system for
security and paramilitary applications.
</P>
<P>
The radar, which was designed to detect and monitor movements
in specific areas, can automatically spot moving targets such as
vehicles, flying helicopters and even people at ranges of up to
10 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The radar could be a tool in the fight against the Lebanese
guerrilla group Hezbollah in south Lebanon, defense officials
said. The radar can also detect packages weighing as little as 20
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The Israel Defense Forces (IDF) will install the radar on its
bases. Elta, IAI's subsidiary, won the IDF radar tender in the
competition that included several international firms, such as
Thomson SA in Paris, the U.S. firm IAL and a British
company. 
</P>
