<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Playing Bigger Role In Northwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region had 82.8 million US dollars in investment from
overseas last year, a record for the region.
</P>
<P>
The sum accounted for a quarter of the region's total
investment in capital construction last year, said Yao Chengsheng,
an official from the regional foreign trade department.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia approved 39 foreign-funded projects, with a contractual
value of 104 million US dollars last year. The amount of foreign
funds actually used in construction each year has risen from 14
percent to 71 percent.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investors have shown growing interest in agriculture,
water conservation, communications, chemicals, and
machinery. Regional economic and trade departments sent
delegations to trade fairs in France, Italy, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait
and Oman and received business people from Japan, the Republic of
Korea and Kuwait last year.
</P>
<P>
The Government of Kuwait provided the region with 140 million
US dollars in loans last year for building a key irrigation
project, which helped one million people in need there to improve
the quality of life. 
</P>
