<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> North China Province Aiming High in Agricultural Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province in north
China has a goal to boost grain and cotton production this year to
28.5 million tons and 300,000 tons respectively.
</P>
<P>
At the Fifth Session of the Eighth Hebei Provincial People's
Congress, Governor Ye Liansong told the assembly that his province
will step up protection of arable land in accordance with the law
and reclaim wasteland to ensure steady agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
In addition to ambitious grain and cotton production goals, the
province plans to produce 1.21 million tons of oil-bearing crops
this year. The governor noted that Hebei is one of the major grain
producers in China, and is famous for the quality of its wheat and
corn.
</P>
<P>
Despite serious flooding in the province last year, Hebei had a
record output of 27.89 million tons of grain, an increase of
500,000 tons over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
So far this year, the province has sown 6.6 million ha in grain,
400,000 ha in cotton, and 600,000 ha in oil-bearing crops.
</P>
<P>
The province is still paying attention to the use of new
agro-technology and prevention from plant diseases and insect
pests.  
</P>
</TEXT>
