<HEADLINE> Good Beginning This Year For Chinese City's Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Industrial production in
Tianjin, one of the largest industrial centers in north China,
reported double-digit growth in January.
</P>
<P>
Gross industrial output totalled 13.69 billion yuan (about 1.6
billion US dollars) last year, a 16.6 percent rise, when figured
in constant prices. Value-added output of enterprises at or above
the township level posted a 14-percent increase at 3.2 billion
yuan, and that of foreign-funded enterprises rose 28.9 percent to
1.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Heavy industry reported 1.98 billion yuan worth of value-added
output while light industry produced 1.18 billion yuan worth.
</P>
<P>
Light industry has surpassed heavy industry in the growth of
value-added production by 4.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The sales ratio for Tianjin's industrial production was 97
percent in January, 1.2 percent higher than for the same period
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
