<HEADLINE> Capital Influx Improving Agriculture in South Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Gaoyao City in south China's
Guangdong Province has made some remarkable progress in
agriculture-related projects by looking for outside investment.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the city's farming sector had used a
total of 88.38 million yuan (10.6 million US dollars) in
investment (including funds from overseas as well as from Chinese
cities) and launched over 20 agricultural projects.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 alone, the city drew an investment of nearly 52 million
yuan, amounting to 58.7 percent of the city's total investment in
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The city's main agricultural sectors, including vegetables,
animal husbandry, aquatics, and grain and fruits, all had a good
year, and total agricultural income hit nearly 7.54 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city has paid attention to developing household farms,
which are expected to reach 400 in number by the end of this
year.  
</P>
