<HEADLINE> India's Rate of Inflation Rises Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 17 (Xinhua) -- Inching its way up, India's
annual rate of inflation rose marginally to 7.73 percent for the
week ended February 1, the Times of India said today.
</P>
<P>
The annual inflation (provisional-over-final) went up by 0.07
percentage points as compared to 7.66 percent during the previous
week.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the wholesale prices index (WPI) for "all
commodities" (base 1981-82=100) also rose marginally by 0.1
percent to 320.6 as against 320.3 for the week before.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, the annual inflation during the corresponding
week in 1996 was 4.7 percent. 
</P>
