<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan army is now
responsible for preserving law and order in the violence ridden
town of Ratnapura, the capital city of Sabaragamuwa province, 110
kilometers from Colombo, according to official sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The army's 11th brigade has deployed troops in the area
following the failure by police to control angry crowds. The
crowds had gone on the rampage, looting and burning buildings
following the assassination of District Member of Parliament
Nalanda Ellawala last Tuesday during political clashes.
</P>
<P>
The army had to rush troops in aid of police at Kuruwita on
Saturday evening when about 750 persons made an attempt to enter
the police station attacking it with stones. Police repelled the
attack with rubber bullets, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bid to storm the police station followed ruling party
activists' attack on the houses and business establishments owned
by the main opposition United National Party supporters.
</P>
<P>
When the mobs tried to storm the police station again, the
police and army were compelled to fire at the mobs during which 2
persons were killed and over 100 persons including several
policemen were injured, the sources added.  
