<HEADLINE> Philippine Muslim Rebels Call off Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, February 17 (Xinhua) -- The Moro Islamic Liberation
Front (MILF) Sunday called off the scheduled low-level talks
between its ceasefire committee and the Philippine government,
local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
MILF vice chairman for political affairs Ghazzali Jaafar said
the postponement was due to an ongoing government military
operation in Shariff Aguak, Maguindanao province and the massive
deployment of government troops in adjacent areas.
</P>
<P>
Jaafar, who is also the MILF chief negotiator, said they has
decided to reset the joint MILF-government technical committee
meeting on February 25 at Sultan Kudarat, Maguindanao.
</P>
<P>
