<HEADLINE> Kasparov Wins Linares Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 16 (Xinhua) -- Garry Kasparov won a chess
tournament in southern Spainish city of Linares on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
He beat his Russian compatriot Vladimir Kramnik in the 11th and
last round to clinch an one-point margin over the closest rival.
</P>
<P>
Kasparov, 33, collected 8.5 points from 11 games, while
21-year-old Kramnik had 7.5.
</P>
<P>
Briton Michael Adams was third and Bulgaria's Veselin Topalov
was fourth.
</P>
<P>
Hungary's Judith Polgar, the only woman in the competition, had
a remarkable performance to place fifth overall.
</P>
