<HEADLINE> Earnings of Township Enterprises in Yunnan Hit All Time High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, February 16 (Xinhua) -- The business earnings of the
township industrial sector in southwest China's border province of
Yunnan have hit an all-time high, according to the latest
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the total earnings of these companies reached 100.4
billion yuan (nearly 10 billion US dollars), a 60 percent increase
over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
To date, both the number of the firms and their employees have
doubled over the 1990 figure. And development of these businesses
in Yunnan started much later than did those in the coastal
provinces in China.
</P>
<P>
The scattered distribution of township enterprises in Yunnan,
44 of which now produce over 100 million yuan (nearly 10 million
US dollars) in annual output, has also changed.
</P>
<P>
"Some 90 zones have been established to accommodate the
concentration of township enterprises in Yunnan," said one official.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the total output of township enterprises
in Yunnan now accounts for more than half of the total rural
output in the province, and their employees make up 17.4 percent
of the total rural labor force.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises are beginning to play a more important
role in the province's industrial sector. "Sixty-three percent of
the province's coal output and some 70 percent of the phosphate
rocks are from the township industrial sector," the official said.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan Provincial Governor He Zhiqiang said the township
enterprises are becoming one of the main economic forces in the
province.
</P>
<P>
"Township enterprises as a whole have brought much vitality to
the overall economic growth of Yunnan, and they are also the main
source of the farmers' income and the main place to absorb the
surplus of rural laborers," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
