<HEADLINE> Tons of Crude Oil Leak Into Russia's Volga River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 16 (Xinhua) -- At least 400 tons of crude oil
has leaked into the River of Volga in Russia after an oil pipeline
broke up on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The pipeline running from Samara to the western Caucasian city
of Tichoreck burst at 11:15 a.m. (Moscow time) on Sunday in the
Ternovka village section in Engel's district of the Saratov
region, Russia's Itar-Tass news agency said.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,200 tons of crude oil had leaked out at 08:00 p.m.,
part of which flowed into the Volga River.
</P>
<P>
An emergency squad had rushed to the site to fight the leakage
which was caused by the pounding of river water according to
initial investigation, the news agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
